    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-05-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-05-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="109"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d109">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Swenson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-05-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 23, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 117.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your No. 204, of the 10th instant, with
                    inclosures, has been received, and your efforts, resulting in permission for
                    Charles C. Rönnow, who was expelled from Denmark last year, to visit the
                    country, have the Department’s approval.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
